Re: Practising via manga
by Mime777 » Wed 06.18.2008 7:38 pm This doesn't really has something to do with practicing with manga but I just m=wanted to know if this sentence was right...私はミリアムです。私はMontréalに"漫画で日本語を学ぼう"を買った。その本は本当にいいですよ。そして、本当にかわいいな服を買った。I wanted to write "I am Myriam(I know this part is right though). In Montréal, I bought "Let's learn Japanese with mangas". This book is really good. I also bought a really nice "piece of clothing".This is a totally useless sentence but I wanted to know if my grammar was correct.
